The original BART model architecture and pre-trained weights are the work of
Facebook AI Research (now Meta AI), published in:

  Lewis, M., Liu, Y., Goyal, N., Ghazvininejad, M., Mohamed, A., Levy, O.,
  Stoyanov, V., & Zettlemoyer, L. (2019). BART: Denoising Sequence-to-Sequence
  Pre-training for Natural Language Generation, Translation, and Comprehension.
  arXiv preprint arXiv:1910.13461. https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.13461

The MNLI fine-tune (`facebook/bart-large-mnli`) is published by Facebook AI
Research at https://huggingface.co/facebook/bart-large-mnli under the MIT
license (declared via the model card YAML front-matter `license: mit`).

This artifact (`bh-healthcare/distilbart-mnli-12-3-int8-onnx`) is an ONNX
export of `facebook/bart-large-mnli` with INT8 dynamic quantization applied
via the `onnxruntime.quantization.quantize_dynamic` tool. The architecture,
weights, and behavior are derived from and substantially identical to the
upstream source. See README.md in this repository for full provenance.

